Iran said it launched a fresh offensivetoday north of Baghdad, three days after it began a new thrustagainst Iraq on the southern Gulf war front.    The Iranian news agency IRNA, received in London, said theoffensive began before dawn northeast of Qasr-e-Shirin, on theborder 110 miles northeast of the Iraqi capital.    "Heavy casualties and losses have been inflicted on Iraqiforces in the fresh Iranian assault," IRNA said.    Iran today reported major gains on the southern front nearthe major Iraqi port city of Basra, saying its forces hadcaptured an important defensive line. REUTER&#3;